# AI-hint: Defines the user-session startup sequence for MiOS, enabling WSLg compatibility, environment injection, and the critical launcher broker/computer-use server for agent-to-host command execution.
# AI-related: mios-wsl-theme-bridge, mios-wsl-graphical-session, mios-wsl-env-import, mios-computer-use-server, mios-launcher, mios-remember, UID.service, mios-wsl-theme-bridge.service, gnome-session.service, mios-wsl-graphical-session.service
# /usr/lib/systemd/user-preset/90-mios.preset
#
# Preset evaluated when systemd's per-user instance (user@$UID.service)
# starts up for the first time. ConditionVirtualization=wsl on the unit
# itself keeps it inert on non-WSL deployments, so enabling it here is
# safe across every MiOS shape.
enable mios-wsl-theme-bridge.service

# WSLg-only graphical-session.target activator. Without this, the
# user-systemd graphical-session.target stays INACTIVE because no
# gnome-session.service exists to pull it in -- which then fails
# every BindsTo=graphical-session.target unit (xdg-desktop-portal-
# gnome and friends), which then cascades dependency failures to
# xdg-desktop-portal frontend, which then takes down every flatpak
# that touches a portal (nautilus / epiphany / gnome-software).
# ConditionPathIsDirectory=/mnt/wslg on the unit gates it to WSLg
# only; bare-metal MiOS keeps the canonical gnome-session activation
# path.
enable mios-wsl-graphical-session.service

# WSLg-only env-import precondition. graphical-session.service
# Requires= this unit so the systemd-user environment carries
# XDG_CURRENT_DESKTOP / WAYLAND_DISPLAY / DISPLAY / XDG_SESSION_TYPE
# before xdg-desktop-portal-gnome activates -- otherwise the portal
# frontend starts but rejects every dbus call from nautilus /
# epiphany / gnome-software with NameHasNoOwner.
enable mios-wsl-env-import.service

# Computer-use node server (dual MCP + A2A + executor for this desktop). Gated
# on the unit by graphical-session.target membership, so it activates only with
# a real Wayland desktop (bare-metal GNOME or WSLg) and stays inert on headless
# nodes. Binds loopback by default; the central agent-pipe consumes it over
# loopback/tailnet (full MCP + A2A federation). Off-switch: disable here or set
# [computer_use].bind_address = "" in mios.toml.
enable mios-computer-use-server.service

# Launcher broker (operator-side; /run/mios-launcher/launcher.sock). The agent
# plane dispatches EVERY host-execution verb (app launch, OS/window control,
# winget, mios-remember, system_status, ...) THROUGH this broker. Without it the
# agent's tool_calls fail with "missing broker socket" and the pipeline cannot
# truly act -- only in-process tools (web_search) work. It runs in the operator's
# session so GUI launches land on their WSLg desktop (never Session 0). Gap found
# on the fresh MiOS-DEV VM 2026-06-05: WantedBy=default.target but never
# preset-enabled, so it never autostarted -> every broker verb failed.
enable mios-launcher.service
